The write command, w, outputs all or part of the data to a file, or
to another edit session.  To output less than the entire data, type
a block address, or a comma separated range of blocks, followed by w.
If you then press enter, Edway writes the data to the default filename
shown as "target" by the question mark command.  To write to a different
file, type a space after the w, the desired filename, then press enter.
To write the data to another edit session instead of to a file, follow
the w with the number of the session, without an intervening space,
then press enter. The session will be created if it does not exist.
Any previous data in the destination session will be overwritten.

